Cosplayers Around the World Feature : Aka from Poland

“Cosplayers Around the World” this week features our first male cosplayer in this column! Today, we go to Poland in winter. For someone like me who have lived by the equator all my life, snow is but a dream come true, with lots of characters in snow settings to be cosplayed as! Albeit, you have…

Competition has finally ended, now comes the exciting part- the results. For this group, here are the top 30 “LIKE” cosplayers in accordance from the 30th finalist to the 1st (at the bottom). This unofficial ranking is based on the vote count as of 2 September 2011, and an epilogue to the months-long voting so…

Leading top 30 North America Cosplay in Album E

So what if the contest has ended, let’s see which cosplay tops this North America Album. Here comes the results for the North America (E) category! May I present you the 30 leading cosplayers in this exciting close-run contest!

Cosplayers Around the World Feature : Danielle LaFleur from USA

After a 2-week hiatus, “Cosplayers Around the World” is back! This issue, we talk to lovely costumer Danielle LaFleur on her cosplay creations which just yells “OMG, look at all that cloth!!”

My favorite part of Gantz

This, and of cause Natsuna Watanabe in the uber tight fitting plug suit. Nuff said.

More photos of Cosplayers and Toys at STGCC 2011 – Zack Part 2

My camera goes all trigger-happy at STGCC! Enjoy the photos of cosplayers and toy figurines available at the show.

Ani Mini Con Review: A chibi con in New York City

Ani Mini Con has proven that great things really do come in small packages. The chibi convention took over the second week of August with three days of art, music and most importantly lots of anime.
